{"title_page": "Yas Island", "text_new": "{{about|the manmade island|the natural island|Sir Bani Yas}}\n{{short description|Island in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{advert|date=August 2018}}\n{{more citations needed|date=February 2012}}\n}}\n[[File:Yas Marina Circuit + Ferrari World -Abu Dhabi.jpg|thumb|View of Yas Island]]\n'''Yas Island''' ({{lang-ar|\u062c\u0632\u064a\u0631\u0629 \u064a\u0627\u0633}}) is an island in [[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasisland.ae/en/maps--tools/maps--directions/ |title=Yas island maps and directions |publisher=yasisland.ae |accessdate=2013-11-12}}</ref>\n\nThe island's development project was initiated in 2006 by Abu Dhabi-based [[Aldar Properties]], with the aim of turning the island into a multi-purpose leisure, shopping and entertainment center at an estimated total cost of over billion.{{clarify|date=August 2018}} This investment was planned as a multi-staged project to unfold in phases until 2018, with project stakeholders foreseeing the possibility of extending development by adding new venues and upgrading existing facilities.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dubaifaqs.com/yas-island.php  |title=Yas Island leisure destination in Abu Dhabi |publisher=dubaifaqs.com |accessdate=2013-11-12}}</ref>\n\nIt occupies a total land area of 2,500 ha (25&nbsp;km\u00b2), of which 1,700 ha will be claimed for development. Yas Island holds the [[Yas Marina Circuit]], which has hosted the [[Formula One]] Etihad Airways [[Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]] since 2009.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nBoth business and leisure travellers visit Yas Island. Yas Island was named the world's leading tourism project at the [[World Travel Awards]] in November 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/yas-island-named-world-s-leading-tourism-project-10964.html |title=Yas Island named World\u2019s Leading Tourism Project |publisher=arabianbusiness.com |date=2009-11-11 |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n==Attractions==\n===Ferrari World===\n{{main|Ferrari World Abu Dhabi}}\nThe Park's foundation stone was laid on 3 November 2007. The development was completed in a little under three years, opening to the public for the first time on November 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ferrariworldabudhabi.com/history/ |title=Ferrari World Abu Dhabi Grand Opening |publisher=ferrariworldabudhabi.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n[[Formula Rossa]], one of the park's most famous attractions, is the world's fastest rollercoaster reaching a speed of 240&nbsp;km/h (149&nbsp;mph).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ferrariworldabudhabi.com/en-gb/attractions/formula-rossa.aspx |title=World's Fastest roller coaster |publisher=ferrariworldabudhabi.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Yas Waterworld ===\n{{main|Yas Waterworld Abu Dhabi}}\nYas Waterworld Surf's up! Bubbles' Barrel slide has the largest surf-able sheet wave surf in the world.\n\n==== Yas Waterworld Awards and Nominations ====\n* Named the \u201csecond best waterpark in the world\u201d by the Los Angeles Times - Global Ranking of the World's Top 20 Waterparks feature in May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/travel/deals/themeparks/la-trb-top-20-water-parks-04201330-pg,0,3909060.photogallery?index=la-trb-top-20-water-parks-04201330-pg-002 |title=Photos: 20 best water parks in the world  |publisher=latimes.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* Listed by CNN as one of the top 12 water parks in the world in July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/31/travel/worlds-best-water-parks/index.html  |title=12 of the world's best water parks  |publisher=edition.cnn.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* Won the World Travel Awards award for the Middle East's Leading Tourist Attraction of the year 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldtravelawards.com/award-middle-easts-leading-tourist-attraction-2013 |title=Middle East's Leading Tourist Attraction 2013  |publisher=worldtravelawards.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* Won the Leading Edge Award at the [[World Waterpark Association]]'s Annual Show, in Las Vegas, USA in October 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yaswaterworld.com/en/news/press-centre/yas-waterworld-abu-dhabi-takes-home-world-waterpark-associations-inaugural-leading-edge-award-1.html |title=Yas Waterworld Abu Dhabi takes home World Waterpark Association\u2019s inaugural Leading Edge Award - Yas Waterworld  |publisher=yaswaterworld.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* The Bandit Bomber is the first rollercoaster to be incorporated into a waterpark and was ranked amongst the world's newest, biggest and baddest roller coasters for the summer of 2013, by CNN.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/05/27/travel/roller-coasters-2013/index.html |title=Newest, biggest, baddest roller coasters for summer  |publisher=edition.cnn.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Warner Bros. World Abu Dhabi ===\n{{main|Warner Bros. World Abu Dhabi}}\nWarner Bros. World Abu Dhabi is located on Yas Island near Ferrari World and Yas Waterworld and was built by [[Miral Asset Management]].<ref name = lat>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-warner-bros-abu-dhabi-20160419-story.html|title=Warner Bros. theme park in Abu Dhabi set to open in 2018|date=April 19, 2016|accessdate=January 27, 2017}}</ref> WB World is organized into six themed lands, Gotham City, Metropolis, Cartoon Junction, Bedrock, Dynamite Gulch and Warner Bros Plaza. Gotham and Metropolis are based on the cities of [[DC Comics]] super heroes [[Batman]] and [[Superman]], respectively. [[Warner Bros.]]'s ''[[Looney Tunes]]'' and [[Hanna-Barbera]] cartoon libraries are featured in Cartoon Junction and Dynamite Gulch except for Bedrock which features the Flintstones. Warner Bros Plaza mimics the Hollywood of the past.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lodderhose|first1=Diana|title=Warner Bros To Build Gotham City & Metropolis For B Abu Dhabi Theme Park|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/warner-bros-world-abu-dhabi-building-real-life-gotham-city-metropolis-1-billion-theme-park-batman-superman-1202076927/|accessdate=April 27, 2017|work=Deadline|publisher=Penske Business Media, LLC|date=April 25, 2017}}</ref> The park opened on July 25, 2018, which makes it the world's third Warner Bros. theme park.<ref name=lat/>\n\n=== SeaWorld Abu Dhabi ===\n{{main|SeaWorld Abu Dhabi}}\nOn December 13, 2016, [[SeaWorld Parks & Entertainment]] announced a new partnership with Miral to bring SeaWorld Abu Dhabi to Yas Island. The park, which will be situated to the northeast of [[Ferrari World]], is set to opened in 2020 and will be the first SeaWorld without [[Killer whale|orcas]].<ref name=\"SeaWorld Abu Dhabi announcement\">{{cite web|title=SeaWorld Announces Partnership with Miral to Develop SeaWorld Abu Dhabi|url=https://seaworldcares.com/seaworldabudhabi|website=seaworldcares.com|publisher=SeaWorld Parks & Entertainment|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"SeaWorld AD-Orlando Sentinel\">{{cite news|last1=Pedicini|first1=Sandra|title=SeaWorld announces new theme park in the Middle East, with no orcas|url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/travel/attractions/seaworld/os-seaworld-theme-park-middle-east-abu-dhabi-20161213-story.html|accessdate=13 December 2016|work=OrlandoSentinel.com}}</ref>\n\n== Sports and Entertainment ==\n\n=== Yas Marina Circuit ===\n{{main|Yas Marina Circuit}}\nThe full circuit length is 5.554&nbsp;km and can be configured in five different ways to accommodate a variety of motorsport events.  Yas Marina Circuit is the only motorsports venue in the world that offers covered and shaded grandstands throughout the facility, coupled with pit lanes that run partially beneath the track.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasmarinacircuit.com/en/about-yas-marina-circuit |title=ABOUT YAS MARINA CIRCUIT  |publisher=yasmarinacircuit.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n==== Other attractions ====\n\nThree charter boat companies operate from Yas Marina namely Jalboot Marine, Captain Tony's and Azure Marine. Seawings operates flights to and from Dubai to Yas Marina and 20 minute Abu Dhabi tours from Yas Marina.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnmarinas.com/en/marinas/yas-marina |title=Welcome to Yas Marina, Abu Dhabi  |publisher=cnmarinas.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Yas Links ===\n\nYas Links is a golf course designed by Kyle Philips, ranked 44th World's 100 Greatest Golf Courses outside the USA (Golf Digest 2018).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.golfdigest.com/story/worlds-100-greatest-golf-courses|title=Ranking: World's 100 Greatest Golf Courses|last=Szurlej|first=Ron Whitten,Dom Furore, Stephen|website=Golf Digest|language=en|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref> 1.8 million cubic metres of material were dredged to form the 18 Hole Championship Golf Course, Golf Club & Golf Shop, pool Area, air-conditioned swing studio and meeting and conference rooms for corporate events.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yaslinks.com |title=Yas Links  |publisher=yaslinks.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\nAs of August 2019, Yas Links Abu Dhabi is now managed by Troon International <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://golfdigestme.com/troon-international-to-manage-middle-east-flagship-venue-yas-links/|title=Troon International to manage Middle East \u2018flagship venue\u2019 Yas Links|date=2019-08-01|website=Golf Digest Middle East|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n=== Yas Beach ===\n\nMangrove Tours launch daily from Yas Beach also courtesy of Noukhada Adventure Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasbeach.ae  |title=Yas Beach|publisher=yasbeach.ae |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== du Live! ===\ndu Live! is an entertainment venue.\n\n====du Arena and Forum====\n[[File:Bocelli-concert-crowd-in-abu-dhabi-du-arena-du-live.jpg|The crowd at Bocelli's concert at du Arena in Abu Dhabi, UAE sponsored by du's entertainment platform du Live!|thumb|alt=The crowd at Bocelli's Concert in du Arena, Abu Dhabi, UAE in 2013]]\n\nThe \"du Arena\" (formerly known as the \"Yas Arena\" until June 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenational.ae/news/uae-news/yas-arena-rebrands-after-deal-with-du |title=Yas Arena rebrands after deal with du |last1=Olson |first1=Mary-Louise |last2= |first2= |date=13 May 2012 |website=The National |publisher=Abu Dhabi Media |accessdate=19 May 2017}}</ref>) is a large open-air concert venue located in Yas Bay. The venue opened in 2009, depending on configuration, the venue can hold up to 35,000. It is coined as the largest open air venue in the Middle East.\n\nThe rebranding preceded the first Madonna concert, part of her [[MDNA Tour]], in the Arab region on 3 and 4 June 2012. du and Think Flash revamped the venue for Madonna's concert, including building up a new 23m x 54m stage and developing a complex pyrotechnic and lighting system. Grass has been relaid, gravel removed, tarmac walkways laid down throughout the arena and a central public plaza area featuring merchandise, retail and entertainment has been installed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/du-arena-gets-revamp-for-madonna-concerts-458086.html|title=Du Arena gets revamp for Madonna concerts|work=ArabianBusiness.com|access-date=2018-11-28|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe arena has hosted many international musicians under the telecom's entertainment platform du Live! in addition to [[Beyonc\u00e9]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], including the [[Rolling Stones]], [[Janet Jackson]], [[Black Sabbath]], [[Eric Clapton]], [[Kylie Minogue]], [[Shakira]], [[Linkin Park]], [[Nickelback]], [[Eminem]], [[Rihanna]], [[Andrea Bocelli]], [[Metallica]], [[Kanye West]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Creamfields]] dance music festival featuring DJs such as Tiesto, [[David Guetta]] and [[Armin Van Buuren]].<ref name=\"http://www.du.ae/en/dulive/Default\">{{cite web|url=http://www.du.ae/en/dulive/Default |title=du Live! |publisher=Du.ae |date= |accessdate=2016-02-25}}</ref> Furthermore, the du Arena has also been the venue for the Middle East's first [[KCON (music festival)|KCON]] event featuring various K-pop artists such as [[Bangtan Boys]], [[Taeyeon]] of [[Girls' Generation]], [[Cho Kyuhyun]] of [[Super Junior]], [[Monsta X]], [[Ailee]], [[SS301]], and [[Spica]] last March 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenational.ae/arts-life/from-korea-with-love-our-guide-to-kcon-2016-in-abu-dhabi|title=From Korea, with love: Our guide to KCON 2016 in Abu Dhabi - The National|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe \"du Forum\" (formerly known as the \"Flash Forum\" until June 2012) is an indoor events venue. It seats up to 4,500. The venues are owned by Adler Properties and operated by [[Comcast Spectacor|Spectra]].\n\n====The du World Music Festival====\nThe du World Music Festival has been organized annually by ''du Live!'' and their partners since 2011. The first du World Music Festival took place at the Burj Khalifa Steps in Downtown Dubai and The Walk in JBR between 26 February to 25 March 2011, with performances by top-class artists from around the world such as [[Tamer Hosny]], Mona Amarcha, Janet Kapuya, [[Mashrou' Leila|Mashrou\u2019 Leila]], Amit Chatterjee Alliance, [[Sponge Cola]], [[Wust El-Balad|Wust el Balad]].\n\nThe second du World Music Festival took place also at the DownTown [[Burj Khalifa]] Steps, took place between 7\u201316 March 2012. Free and ticketed events included performances by Gabrielle, The Gipsy Kings, Amr Diab, Rahat Fateh Ali Khan, Stanley Clarke, Salif Keita, Sarah Geronimo, George Benson.\n\nThe third du World Music Festival took place between 22 March 2013 - 6 April 2013, and included famous names as [[Andrea Bocelli]], [[Natalie Cole]], [[Guns N\u2019 Roses]], [[Kadim Al Sahir]], [[Amr Diab]], [[Eraserheads]], [[Sonu Nigam]], Train, [[Frank Gambale]], Papon among others. This edition included performances at the du Arena in [[Abu Dhabi]], the [[Dubai Media City]] Amphitheatre in [[Dubai]], and in [[Ras Al Khaimah]].\n\n== Hotels ==\n\n=== Yas Viceroy Abu Dhabi ===\n[[Yas Hotel Abu Dhabi]] is a five star hotel located on the Yas Marina and is the first hotel in world to be built over an [[F1]] race circuit.\n\n=== Yas Plaza Hotels ===\nThe seven Yas Plaza hotels includes:\n* [[Crowne Plaza Abu Dhabi Yas Island]]\n* [[Staybridge Suites Abu Dhabi Yas Island]]\n* Radisson Blu Abu Dhabi Yas Island\n* Park Inn Abu Dhabi Yas Island\n* Rotana Yas Island\n* Centro Yas Island\n* Warner Bros Hotel Abu Dhabi Yas Island\n\n== Transportation ==\n\n=== Yas Express ===\n\nYas express Saadiyat route shuttle service is the latest route (launched July 1) which interlinks St. Regis Saadiyat Island Resort and Park Hyatt Abu Dhabi with Yas Island's attractions. Operating daily with 3 pickups in the morning and 3 drop offs in the afternoon, the shuttle service transports guests to Ferrari World Abu Dhabi and Yas Waterworld, Yas Island. The afternoon service offers three pickups from Ferrari World Abu Dhabi, dropping visitors back to each of the respective resorts on Saadiyat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasisland.ae/en/maps--tools/yas-express-/ |title=Yas Express  |publisher=yasisland.ae |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n== Retail ==\n\n=== Yas Mall ===\nYas Mall is one of Abu Dhabi's largest malls, located close to IKEA. In January 2017, Forbes recognized Yas Mall as one of the top five shopping malls in Abu Dhabi.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bishopjordan/2017/01/03/best-shopping-malls-abu-dhabi/ |title=The Five Best Shopping Malls In Abu Dhabi |accessdate=2017-01-08}}</ref>\n\n=== IKEA ===\nIKEA Yas Island is the flagship store and first retail outlet to open on Yas Island. The 33,000 sqm store with a total sales area of 19,150sqm is the largest IKEA store in the [[MENA]] region and includes a play area for kids.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ikea.com/ae/en/store/abu_dhabi |title=IKEA Yas Island   |publisher=ikea.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref> Previously located within the Marina Mall complex, the store was moved to Yas Island primarily due to limited room for expansion.\n\n=== ACE Hardware ===\nThe ACE Hardware Yas Island is the UAE's second largest ACE Hardware store, with 5,200 square meters of retail space.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.aceuae.com/en/ace-uae |title=Ace UAE   |publisher=aceuae.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Developments in Abu Dhabi}}\n{{Abu Dhabi}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures under construction in Abu Dhabi]]\n[[Category:Islands of Abu Dhabi (emirate)]]\n[[Category:Artificial islands of the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Central Region, Abu Dhabi]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Island in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates}}\n{{about|the manmade island|the natural island|Sir Bani Yas}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{ad|date=August 2018}}\n{{more citations needed|date=February 2012}}\n}}\n[[File:Yas Marina Circuit + Ferrari World -Abu Dhabi.jpg|thumb|View of Yas Island]]\n'''Yas Island''' ({{lang-ar|\u062c\u0632\u064a\u0631\u0629 \u064a\u0627\u0633}}) is an island in [[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasisland.ae/en/maps--tools/maps--directions/ |title=Yas island maps and directions |publisher=yasisland.ae |accessdate=2013-11-12}}</ref>\n\nThe island\u2019s development project was initiated in 2006 by Abu Dhabi-based [[Aldar Properties]], with the aim of turning the island into a multi-purpose leisure, shopping and entertainment center at an estimated total cost of over billion.{{what|date=August 2018}} This investment was planned as a multi-staged project to unfold in phases until 2018, with project stakeholders foreseeing the possibility of extending development by adding new venues and upgrading existing facilities.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dubaifaqs.com/yas-island.php  |title=Yas Island leisure destination in Abu Dhabi |publisher=dubaifaqs.com |accessdate=2013-11-12}}</ref>\n\nIt occupies a total land area of 2,500 ha (25 km\u00b2), of which 1,700 ha will be claimed for development. Yas Island holds the [[Yas Marina Circuit]], which has hosted the [[Formula One]] Etihad Airways [[Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]] since 2009.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nBoth business and leisure travellers visit Yas Island. Yas Island was named the world's leading tourism project at the [[World Travel Awards]] in November 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/yas-island-named-world-s-leading-tourism-project-10964.html |title=Yas Island named World\u2019s Leading Tourism Project |publisher=arabianbusiness.com |date=2009-11-11 |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n==Attractions==\n===Ferrari World===\n{{main|Ferrari World Abu Dhabi}}\nThe Park\u2019s foundation stone was laid on 3 November 2007. The development was completed in a little under three years, opening to the public for the first time on November 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ferrariworldabudhabi.com/history/ |title=Ferrari World Abu Dhabi Grand Opening |publisher=ferrariworldabudhabi.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n[[Formula Rossa]], one of the park's most famous attractions, is the world\u2019s fastest rollercoaster reaching a speed of 240&nbsp;km/h (149&nbsp;mph).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ferrariworldabudhabi.com/en-gb/attractions/formula-rossa.aspx |title=World's Fastest roller coaster |publisher=ferrariworldabudhabi.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Yas Waterworld ===\n{{main|Yas Waterworld Abu Dhabi}}\nYas Waterworld Surf\u2019s up! Bubbles' Barrel slide has the largest surf-able sheet wave surf in the world.\n\n==== Yas Waterworld Awards and Nominations ====\n* Named the \u201csecond best waterpark in the world\u201d by the Los Angeles Times - Global Ranking of the World\u2019s Top 20 Waterparks feature in May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/travel/deals/themeparks/la-trb-top-20-water-parks-04201330-pg,0,3909060.photogallery?index=la-trb-top-20-water-parks-04201330-pg-002 |title=Photos: 20 best water parks in the world  |publisher=latimes.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* Listed by CNN as one of the top 12 water parks in the world in July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/31/travel/worlds-best-water-parks/index.html  |title=12 of the world's best water parks  |publisher=edition.cnn.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* Won the World Travel Awards award for the Middle East\u2019s Leading Tourist Attraction of the year 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldtravelawards.com/award-middle-easts-leading-tourist-attraction-2013 |title=Middle East's Leading Tourist Attraction 2013  |publisher=worldtravelawards.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* Won the Leading Edge Award at the [[World Waterpark Association]]'s Annual Show, in Las Vegas, USA in October 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yaswaterworld.com/en/news/press-centre/yas-waterworld-abu-dhabi-takes-home-world-waterpark-associations-inaugural-leading-edge-award-1.html |title=Yas Waterworld Abu Dhabi takes home World Waterpark Association\u2019s inaugural Leading Edge Award - Yas Waterworld  |publisher=yaswaterworld.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n* The Bandit Bomber is the first rollercoaster to be incorporated into a waterpark and was ranked amongst the world\u2019s newest, biggest and baddest roller coasters for the summer of 2013, by CNN.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/05/27/travel/roller-coasters-2013/index.html |title=Newest, biggest, baddest roller coasters for summer  |publisher=edition.cnn.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Warner Bros. World Abu Dhabi ===\n{{main|Warner Bros. World Abu Dhabi}}\nWarner Bros. World Abu Dhabi is located on Yas Island near Ferrari World and Yas Waterworld and was built by [[Miral Asset Management]].<ref name = lat>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-warner-bros-abu-dhabi-20160419-story.html|title=Warner Bros. theme park in Abu Dhabi set to open in 2018|date=April 19, 2016|accessdate=January 27, 2017}}</ref> WB World is organized into six themed lands, Gotham City, Metropolis, Cartoon Junction, Bedrock, Dynamite Gulch and Warner Bros Plaza. Gotham and Metropolis are based on the cities of [[DC Comics]] super heroes [[Batman]] and [[Superman]], respectively. [[Warner Bros.]]'s ''[[Looney Tunes]]'' and [[Hanna-Barbera]] cartoon libraries are featured in Cartoon Junction and Dynamite Gulch except for Bedrock which features the Flintstones. Warner Bros Plaza mimics the Hollywood of the past.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lodderhose|first1=Diana|title=Warner Bros To Build Gotham City & Metropolis For B Abu Dhabi Theme Park|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/warner-bros-world-abu-dhabi-building-real-life-gotham-city-metropolis-1-billion-theme-park-batman-superman-1202076927/|accessdate=April 27, 2017|work=Deadline|publisher=Penske Business Media, LLC|date=April 25, 2017}}</ref> The park opened on July 25, 2018, which makes it the world's third Warner Bros. theme park.<ref name=lat/>\n\n=== SeaWorld Abu Dhabi ===\n{{main article|SeaWorld Abu Dhabi}}\nOn December 13, 2016, [[SeaWorld Parks & Entertainment]] announced a new partnership with Miral to bring SeaWorld Abu Dhabi to Yas Island. The park, which will be situated to the northeast of [[Ferrari World]], is set to opened in 2020 and will be the first SeaWorld without [[Killer whale|orcas]].<ref name=\"SeaWorld Abu Dhabi announcement\">{{cite web|title=SeaWorld Announces Partnership with Miral to Develop SeaWorld Abu Dhabi|url=https://seaworldcares.com/seaworldabudhabi|website=seaworldcares.com|publisher=SeaWorld Parks & Entertainment|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"SeaWorld AD-Orlando Sentinel\">{{cite news|last1=Pedicini|first1=Sandra|title=SeaWorld announces new theme park in the Middle East, with no orcas|url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/travel/attractions/seaworld/os-seaworld-theme-park-middle-east-abu-dhabi-20161213-story.html|accessdate=13 December 2016|work=OrlandoSentinel.com}}</ref>\n\n== Sports and Entertainment ==\n\n=== Yas Marina Circuit ===\n{{main|Yas Marina Circuit}}\nThe full circuit length is 5.554&nbsp;km and can be configured in five different ways to accommodate a variety of motorsport events.  Yas Marina Circuit is the only motorsports venue in the world that offers covered and shaded grandstands throughout the facility, coupled with pit lanes that run partially beneath the track.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasmarinacircuit.com/en/about-yas-marina-circuit |title=ABOUT YAS MARINA CIRCUIT  |publisher=yasmarinacircuit.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n==== Other attractions ====\n\nThree charter boat companies operate from Yas Marina namely Jalboot Marine, Captain Tony's and Azure Marine. Seawings operates flights to and from Dubai to Yas Marina and 20 minute Abu Dhabi tours from Yas Marina.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnmarinas.com/en/marinas/yas-marina |title=Welcome to Yas Marina, Abu Dhabi  |publisher=cnmarinas.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== Yas Links ===\n\nYas Links is a golf course designed by Kyle Philips, ranked 44th World\u2019s 100 Greatest Golf Courses outside the USA (Golf Digest 2018)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.golfdigest.com/story/worlds-100-greatest-golf-courses|title=Ranking: World's 100 Greatest Golf Courses|last=Szurlej|first=Ron Whitten,Dom Furore, Stephen|website=Golf Digest|language=en|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>. 1.8 million cubic metres of material were dredged to form the 18 Hole Championship Golf Course, Golf Club & Golf Shop, pool Area, air-conditioned swing studio and meeting and conference rooms for corporate events.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yaslinks.com |title=Yas Links  |publisher=yaslinks.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\nAs of August 2019, Yas Links Abu Dhabi is now manged by Troon International <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://golfdigestme.com/troon-international-to-manage-middle-east-flagship-venue-yas-links/|title=Troon International to manage Middle East \u2018flagship venue\u2019 Yas Links|date=2019-08-01|website=Golf Digest Middle East|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n\n=== Yas Beach ===\n\nMangrove Tours launch daily from Yas Beach also courtesy of Noukhada Adventure Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasbeach.ae  |title=Yas Beach|publisher=yasbeach.ae |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n=== du Live! ===\ndu Live! is an entertainment venue.\n\n====du Arena and Forum====\n[[File:Bocelli-concert-crowd-in-abu-dhabi-du-arena-du-live.jpg|The crowd at Bocelli's concert at du Arena in Abu Dhabi, UAE sponsored by du's entertainment platform du Live!|thumb|alt=The crowd at Bocelli's Concert in du Arena, Abu Dhabi, UAE in 2013]]\n\nThe \"du Arena\" (formerly known as the \"Yas Arena\" until June 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenational.ae/news/uae-news/yas-arena-rebrands-after-deal-with-du |title=Yas Arena rebrands after deal with du |last1=Olson |first1=Mary-Louise |last2= |first2= |date=13 May 2012 |website=The National |publisher=Abu Dhabi Media |accessdate=19 May 2017}}</ref>) is a large open-air concert venue located in Yas Bay. The venue opened in 2009, depending on configuration, the venue can hold up to 35,000. It is coined as the largest open air venue in the Middle East.\n\nThe rebranding preceded the first Madonna concert, part of her [[MDNA Tour]], in the Arab region on 3 and 4 June 2012. du and Think Flash revamped the venue for Madonna\u2019s concert, including building up a new 23m x 54m stage and developing a complex pyrotechnic and lighting system. Grass has been relaid, gravel removed, tarmac walkways laid down throughout the arena and a central public plaza area featuring merchandise, retail and entertainment has been installed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/du-arena-gets-revamp-for-madonna-concerts-458086.html|title=Du Arena gets revamp for Madonna concerts|work=ArabianBusiness.com|access-date=2018-11-28|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe arena has hosted many international musicians under the telecom\u2019s entertainment platform du Live! in addition to [[Beyonc\u00e9]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], including the [[Rolling Stones]], [[Janet Jackson]], [[Black Sabbath]], [[Eric Clapton]], [[Kylie Minogue]], [[Shakira]], [[Linkin Park]], [[Nickelback]], [[Eminem]], [[Rihanna]], [[Andrea Bocelli]], [[Metallica]], [[Kanye West]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Creamfields]] dance music festival featuring DJs such as Tiesto, [[David Guetta]] and [[Armin Van Buuren]].<ref name=\"http://www.du.ae/en/dulive/Default\">{{cite web|url=http://www.du.ae/en/dulive/Default |title=du Live! |publisher=Du.ae |date= |accessdate=2016-02-25}}</ref> Furthermore, the du Arena has also been the venue for the Middle East's first [[KCON (music festival)|KCON]] event featuring various K-pop artists such as [[Bangtan Boys]], [[Taeyeon]] of [[Girls' Generation]], [[Cho Kyuhyun]] of [[Super Junior]], [[Monsta X]], [[Ailee]], [[SS301]], and [[Spica]] last March 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenational.ae/arts-life/from-korea-with-love-our-guide-to-kcon-2016-in-abu-dhabi|title=From Korea, with love: Our guide to KCON 2016 in Abu Dhabi - The National|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe \"du Forum\" (formerly known as the \"Flash Forum\" until June 2012) is an indoor events venue. It seats up to 4,500. The venues are owned by Adler Properties and operated by [[Comcast Spectacor|Spectra]].\n\n====The du World Music Festival====\nThe du World Music Festival has been organized annually by ''du Live!'' and their partners since 2011. The first du World Music Festival took place at the Burj Khalifa Steps in Downtown Dubai and The Walk in JBR between 26 February to 25 March 2011, with performances by top-class artists from around the world such as [[Tamer Hosny]], Mona Amarcha, Janet Kapuya, [[Mashrou' Leila|Mashrou\u2019 Leila]], Amit Chatterjee Alliance, [[Sponge Cola]], [[Wust El-Balad|Wust el Balad]].\n\nThe second du World Music Festival took place also at the DownTown [[Burj Khalifa]] Steps, took place between 7\u201316 March 2012. Free and ticketed events included performances by Gabrielle, The Gipsy Kings, Amr Diab, Rahat Fateh Ali Khan, Stanley Clarke, Salif Keita, Sarah Geronimo, George Benson.\n\nThe third du World Music Festival took place between 22 March 2013 - 6 April 2013, and included famous names as [[Andrea Bocelli]], [[Natalie Cole]], [[Guns N\u2019 Roses]], [[Kadim Al Sahir]], [[Amr Diab]], [[Eraserheads]], [[Sonu Nigam]], Train, [[Frank Gambale]], Papon among others. This edition included performances at the du Arena in [[Abu Dhabi]], the [[Dubai Media City]] Amphitheatre in [[Dubai]], and in [[Ras Al Khaimah]].\n\n== Hotels ==\n\n=== Yas Viceroy Abu Dhabi ===\n[[Yas Hotel Abu Dhabi]] is a five star hotel located on the Yas Marina and is the first hotel in world to be built over an [[F1]] race circuit.\n\n=== Yas Plaza Hotels ===\nThe seven Yas Plaza hotels includes:\n* [[Crowne Plaza Abu Dhabi Yas Island]]\n* [[Staybridge Suites Abu Dhabi Yas Island]]\n* Radisson Blu Abu Dhabi Yas Island\n* Park Inn Abu Dhabi Yas Island\n* Rotana Yas Island\n* Centro Yas Island\n* Warner Bros Hotel Abu Dhabi Yas Island\n\n== Transportation ==\n\n=== Yas Express ===\n\nYas express Saadiyat route shuttle service is the latest route (launched July 1) which interlinks St. Regis Saadiyat Island Resort and Park Hyatt Abu Dhabi with Yas Island\u2019s attractions. Operating daily with 3 pickups in the morning and 3 drop offs in the afternoon, the shuttle service transports guests to Ferrari World Abu Dhabi and Yas Waterworld, Yas Island. The afternoon service offers three pickups from Ferrari World Abu Dhabi, dropping visitors back to each of the respective resorts on Saadiyat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yasisland.ae/en/maps--tools/yas-express-/ |title=Yas Express  |publisher=yasisland.ae |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n== Retail ==\n\n=== Yas Mall ===\nYas Mall is one of Abu Dhabi's largest malls, located close to IKEA. In January 2017, Forbes recognized Yas Mall as one of the top five shopping malls in Abu Dhabi.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bishopjordan/2017/01/03/best-shopping-malls-abu-dhabi/ |title=The Five Best Shopping Malls In Abu Dhabi |accessdate=2017-01-08}}</ref>\n\n=== IKEA ===\nIKEA Yas Island is the flagship store and first retail outlet to open on Yas Island. The 33,000 sqm store with a total sales area of 19,150sqm is the largest IKEA store in the [[MENA]] region and includes a play area for kids.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ikea.com/ae/en/store/abu_dhabi |title=IKEA Yas Island   |publisher=ikea.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref> Previously located within the Marina Mall complex, the store was moved to Yas Island primarily due to limited room for expansion.\n\n=== ACE Hardware ===\nThe ACE Hardware Yas Island is the UAE\u2019s second largest ACE Hardware store, with 5,200 square meters of retail space.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.aceuae.com/en/ace-uae |title=Ace UAE   |publisher=aceuae.com |accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Developments in Abu Dhabi}}\n{{Abu Dhabi}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures under construction in Abu Dhabi]]\n[[Category:Islands of Abu Dhabi (emirate)]]\n[[Category:Artificial islands of the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Central Region, Abu Dhabi]]\n", "name_user": "Nat965", "label": "safe", "comment": "ApplyGen fix(es),typo(s) fixed: manged \u2192 managed, \u2019s \u2192 's (12)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yas_Island"}
